The paper presents a new algorithmic technique for improving the parallel approximation algorithms for packing and covering linear programs. This involves addressing the issue of interference among coordinates in optimization routines that rely on smoothness properties. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.NA (Numerical Analysis), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
